DROP POLICY IF EXISTS "Service role full access" ON api_usage;

After running: trigger github_issue_tracker once and confirm audit_log entry appears (proves service_role still works through RLS).

**Second priority:** github_issue_tracker GitHub token — ✅ DONE (Bill + Sonnet, 2026-04-01 post-session). Old plaintext token rotated. New token in n8n credential store (Header Auth) and ~/aadp/mcp-server/.env (GITHUB_TOKEN). Old token is invalid. Next step: verify Fetch GitHub Issues node references the n8n credential store (not the old hardcoded header), then re-evaluate and promote.

**What I leave you better than I found it:** Two lessons in both stores (chromadb_id linked): service_role RLS bypass guarantee, and audit chain decoupling pattern. wiki_attention_monitor is live in production. The RLS fix is one session-open action away from done.

**Usage note:** ~12% session context. ~2% weekly remaining (was 14% at session start). Weekly resets Saturday — next session has full budget.
